Energy Department Reduces 2011 Natural Gas Price Forecast

-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   B u u r m a
-- 
2011-03-08T17:09:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/energy-department-reduces-2011-natural-gas-price-forecast.html
Gas prices at the benchmark  Henry
Hub  in Erath, Louisiana, will average $4.10 per million British
thermal units this year, down from February’s estimate of $4.16,
according to the report from the Energy Department’s Energy
Information Administration. Prices averaged $4.39 in 2010.  Natural gas for April delivery rose 2.1 cents, 0.5 percent,
to $3.948 per million Btu at 12:05 p.m. on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange . Prices have declined 10 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Buurma in New York at 
 cbuurma1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net  